edu.umn.biomedicus.common.viterbi

Class Viterbi

  • edu.umn.biomedicus.common.viterbi.Viterbi

  • public class Viterbi

    Constructor class for viterbi processors.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Static Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static <S> CandidateProbability<S> candidateOf()
      Creates a new CandidateProbability of a candidate-state and an emission probable for that candidate state. This method would be used when a EmissionProbabilityModel needs to a provide a CandidateProbability to the viterbi processor.
      static <S,Y> ViterbiProcessor<S,Y> firstOrder()
      Creates a new first-order ViterbiProcessor. A first order viterbi processor only relies on the most recent state to compute transition probabilities, and only stores the most probable sequence for each possible most recent state for each step of computation.
      static <S,Y> ViterbiProcessor<S,Y> secondOrder()
      Creates a new second-order ViterbiProcessor. A second order viterbi processor relies on the two most recent hidden states, and stores the most probable sequence for each possible permutation of the two most recent states at each step of computation.

    • Method Detail

      • firstOrder

        public static <S,Y> ViterbiProcessor<S,Y> firstOrder()

        Creates a new first-order ViterbiProcessor. A first order viterbi processor only relies on the most recent state to compute transition probabilities, and only stores the most probable sequence for each possible most recent state for each step of computation.

        Returns:
        ViterbiProcessor which consumes emitted values and computes the most probable hidden state sequence.

      • secondOrder

        public static <S,Y> ViterbiProcessor<S,Y> secondOrder()

        Creates a new second-order ViterbiProcessor. A second order viterbi processor relies on the two most recent hidden states, and stores the most probable sequence for each possible permutation of the two most recent states at each step of computation.

        Returns:
        ViterbiProcessor which consumes emitted values and computes most probable hidden state sequence.

      • candidateOf

        public static <S> CandidateProbability<S> candidateOf()

        Creates a new CandidateProbability of a candidate-state and an emission probable for that candidate state. This method would be used when a EmissionProbabilityModel needs to a provide a CandidateProbability to the viterbi processor.

        Returns:
        newly created Candidate object that stores the parameters.
